1. *Čuju* se zvuci gitare iz parka. (You can hear the sound of a guitar from the park.)
2. Da li *čuju* naši prijatelji muziku koju puštamo? (Can our friends hear the music we're playing?)
3. *Čujem* da će sutra biti sunčano. (I hear that it will be sunny tomorrow.)
4. Niko nije želeo da *čuje* o njegovom planu. (No one wanted to hear about his plan.)
5. Kada sam ušao u sobu, *čuo* sam neobičan zvuk. (When I entered the room, I heard a strange noise.)
6. Moji roditelji me nikada nisu *čuli* kada sam imao problema. (My parents never listened to me when I had problems.)
7. *Čuješ* li ti mene ili samo misliš na nešto drugo? (Are you listening to me or are you thinking about something else?)
8. Molim te, *čuj* me ovo jednom. (Please, listen to me just this once.)
9. Oni *čuju* glasove ljudi iz susjedne sobe. (They can hear voices of people from the neighboring room.)
10. Udaljeni zvuk sirene se *čuo* iz daljine. (The distant sound of the siren was audible.)

Note: The word "čuju" is a conjugation of the Serbian verb "čuti" which means "to hear" in English.